    Pagecord: A Better Medium Alternative
  </h1>

  <div class="md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4 mt-8 md:mt-12">
    <p>
      Medium locks your writing behind a paywall. Your readers get three free articles a month, then hit a wall. They get bombarded with popups begging them to sign up. You don't own your domain or your content.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pagecord is the opposite. Your readers never hit a paywall. Zero popups. You own your domain. You can export everything as HTML or Markdown anytime. Plus you can blog by email—just hit send and you're published.
    </p>
    <p>
      Open source. Classic plan is free forever. Premium is $<%= localised_price %>/year.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-8 mb-4 md:text-xl">
    <%= link_to new_signup_path do %>
      <div class="mt-2 inline-flex font-medium p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm btn-primary text-xl">Get your FREE account today</div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

